#compiler #llvm #ir

Instrumenting functions' prologue and epilogue is not as straight forward as it
seem.

To instrument every function's prologue:

```cpp
  auto FirstI = &*F.getEntryBlock().begin();
  IRBuilder<> ProIRB(FirstI);
  CallInst *Prologue = ProIRB.CreateCall(CapacPrologue);

  DILocation *Loc =
      DILocation::get(F.getParent()->getContext(), 0, 0, F.getSubprogram());
  Prologue->setDebugLoc(Loc);
```

Note that The debug location is needed because of this error:

> inlinable function call in a function with debug info must have a !dbg
> location

The epilogue must cover all exit points of the function. This can be done by
scanning for return instructions in the basic blocks.

```cpp

   // Collect possible exit points
   std::vector<BasicBlock *> ReturningBlocks;
   for (BasicBlock &I : F)
     if (isa<ReturnInst>(I.getTerminator()))
       ReturningBlocks.push_back(&I);

   // Insert epilogue to all blocks
   if (ReturningBlocks.size() != 0) {
     for (BasicBlock *BB : ReturningBlocks) {
       IRBuilder<> EpiIRB(BB->getTerminator());
       CallInst *Epi = EpiIRB.CreateCall(CapacEpilogue);
       Epi->setDebugLoc(EpiIRB.getCurrentDebugLocation());
     }
   }
```

