#area #tikz #latex

# Arrow
## Ankles
There are several ways to add ankle to tikz arrows. All of them are non-trivial (like just changing the arrow types in most diagram makers.)

### Relative coordinate
You can use relative addressing to address the point between two nodes. However, this require some manual adjustment.

```tikz
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\node(a) at (0,0) {A};
\node(b) at (2,2) {B};
\draw[->] (a) -| ++(1,1) |- (b);
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

### Calculating middle point 
This requires the `calc` tikz library.
```tikz
\usetikzlibrary{calc}
\begin{document}
\begin{tikzpicture}
\node(a) at (0,0) {A};
\node(b) at (2,2) {B};
\draw[->] (a) -| ($(a)!0.5!(b)$) |- (b);
\end{tikzpicture}
\end{document}
```

